{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d09233b8-32b7-46af-b233-4792bc71f219","content":"Yes, you'll hit framework compatibility issues. MSTest v3 requires:\n\n- **.NET Framework 4.6.2+** — your `net462` is fine ✅\n- **.NET 6.0+** — your `net5.0` ❌ and `netcoreapp3.1` ❌ are **not supported**\n\n**To migrate, you'd need to:**\n\n1. **Update target frameworks** — replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with supported versions (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. **Simplify packages** — MSTest v3 offers a single `MSTest` meta-package replacing the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` references.\n\n**Other breaking changes to watch for** in v3 include removal of some deprecated APIs, stricter lifecycle semantics for `[ClassInitialize]`/`[ClassCleanup]`, and behavioral changes around `Assert.ThrowsException`. Review the [MSTest v3 migration guide](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/mstest-sdk-overview) before upgrading.\n\nWould you like me to update the project file for MSTest v3?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"85674d44-2b87-4991-9637-bf69cff0f184","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a project targeting `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nKey compatibility issues with MSTest v3:\n\n1. **Dropped framework support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's end-of-life)\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` is no longer supported (end-of-life)\n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` (`net462`) — MSTest v3 requires at minimum .NET Framework 4.6.2, so this one should still be supported. Actually, let me think about this more carefully. MSTest v3 supports .NET Framework 4.6.2+, so `net462` should be fine.\n   \nSo to clarify the actual support matrix: MSTest v3 requires .NET Framework 4.6.2 or higher for the framework side, and .NET 6.0 or later for the .NET Core/.NET versions. This means `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` both need to be upgraded to at least `net6.0`, while `net462` remains compatible. MSTest v3 also consolidates its package structure, moving away from separate `MSTest.TestFramework` packages.\n\nBeyond the framework requirements, there are several breaking changes to be aware of—some APIs have been removed or modified, `Assert.ThrowsException` behaves differently, `DataRow` attributes work differently, and the class/assembly cleanup and initialization methods have changed.","outputTokens":759,"requestId":"0831:1660D8:851D53D:9413D4C:69EAD580"},"id":"cd8461f2-8156-455e-9928-36aa7475ab27","timestamp":"2026-04-24T02:29:37.358Z","parentId":"400598e5-c9bc-49f3-94f6-2701a8ec5558"}
